    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.7.0-dev+1319-gb81c310d4\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nWindows 10\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\nHaving a buffer with the content:\r\n```\r\nfoo\r\nbar\r\n```\r\nAfter `:clearjumps`, navigate to `r` in `bar`, without jumping. Press ``m` ``. Navigate to\r\nsome position on the first line, w/o jumping. Pressing `<c-o>` jumps to `r`.\r\n\r\nRepeat the same process, but use ``:lua vim.api.nvim_buf_set_mark(0, '`', 2, 2, {})``.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`<c-o>` should jump to the position of the `` ` `` mark.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nPressing `<c-o>` has no effect. ``` `` ``` works as expected.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The bug happens because context marks \"live in the window\" not in the buffer like the jumplist. That's one of the reasons `nvim_buf_set_mark` has an opts parameter but It hasn't been implemented.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/09524c12f8571156b807d4fd4cc8afc31f91c025/src/nvim/mark.c#L102-L111\r\n\r\nThe logic that decides to run `setpcmark()` is false in this case. It requires a refactor so that `setpcmark` or an auxiliary function takes as argument a window, buffer and position.",
